    <briefdescription>
<para>A single host:port pair parsed from an HMS URI. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>HMS URIs commonly take one of the forms:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>thrift://host:port</computeroutput> (Java <ref refid="classiceberg_1_1hive_1_1HiveCatalog" kindref="compound">HiveCatalog</ref> convention)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>host:port</computeroutput> (iceberg-rust HmsCatalog convention)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>comma-separated list of either form for HA failover</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><computeroutput>port</computeroutput> defaults to 9083 (Hive&apos;s well-known metastore port) when the caller omits an explicit port. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
